      <processinfo id="aspace_f5dc1a83f54922e964881195491371d0">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_a25b39b53b67fa8c01187e2ff1053b3c">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of development files, committee records, financial reports, budgets, and notes of the deputy university librarian, Yale University. The records document library departments and collections, personnel, equipment requests, and the library's participation in the Research Libraries Group (RLG).</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_9d93cdea81d1e048b7bd270e165820c1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by subject.</p>  
      </arrangement>
